  "text": "Oryza sativa cultivar Nipponbare seeds were husked and sterilized as described above, and placed on a filter paper (25 seeds/paper, 9 cm diameter). Five milliliters of washed microbial cell suspension (OD 600 = 1.0) of the selected strains were added to the paper, and the seeds were allowed to germinate for 4 d under the same condition as above. The seedlings were then transferred onto a plastic mesh floated on Kimura B medium [CITATION_1] Fertilizer was not applied. After 4 months, the inoculation effect was evaluated as the means of measuring shoot dry weight, number and weight of panicles, grains, and ripened grains. Grains that sank in water of density 1.06 (60 g/l NaCl) were regarded as ripened grains.",
